{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Best Classifier?","date":"06-11-2019"},"html":"<p>Let's talk about the Bayesian classifier in detail today. At the end, you can decide if it is the best classifier!\n<span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 68.25396825396825%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"first\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/2fb4f6a2328de834d18d7143db23e210/a66cd/first.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2fb4f6a2328de834d18d7143db23e210/4272c/first.jpg 188w,\n/static/2fb4f6a2328de834d18d7143db23e210/1459e/first.jpg 375w,\n/static/2fb4f6a2328de834d18d7143db23e210/a66cd/first.jpg 750w,\n/static/2fb4f6a2328de834d18d7143db23e210/c0626/first.jpg 1125w,\n/static/2fb4f6a2328de834d18d7143db23e210/73ada/first.jpg 1386w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p>Let's say we have a two dimensional feature space, with feature vectors [x,y]. We also have the training set that is labeled. The label consists of two classes, <span style=\"color:blue\">blue</span> and <span style=\"color:red\">red</span>.</p>\n<p>Here is your task: I give you a feature vector, can you tell me which class this feature vector belongs to? I also want to know the decision boundary you used to determine the class. Is this a simple task?</p>\n<p>In other words, would you classify the grey point below as class <span style=\"color:blue\">blue</span> or class <span style=\"color:red\">red</span>?</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 65.63275434243177%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"second\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/2be8d6ded96bc57ae2db77590c58e5ce/a66cd/second.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2be8d6ded96bc57ae2db77590c58e5ce/4272c/second.jpg 188w,\n/static/2be8d6ded96bc57ae2db77590c58e5ce/1459e/second.jpg 375w,\n/static/2be8d6ded96bc57ae2db77590c58e5ce/a66cd/second.jpg 750w,\n/static/2be8d6ded96bc57ae2db77590c58e5ce/c0626/second.jpg 1125w,\n/static/2be8d6ded96bc57ae2db77590c58e5ce/45751/second.jpg 1500w,\n/static/2be8d6ded96bc57ae2db77590c58e5ce/8c402/second.jpg 1612w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p>In this post, you are going to learn:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bayesian classifiers - best classifier in the world?</li>\n<li>Discriminant function - how to calculate the decision surfaces?</li>\n<li>Linear vs quatric decision surfaces - what is the difference?</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Bayesian classifiers</h2>\n<p>I asked a friend who knows nothing about classifiers to tell me which class the gray point belongs to. He said it looks like it belongs to class red due to how each class \"centers\" and the \"spread.\" Then he said he basically compares the standard deviations. Little did he know, what he described is exactly the intuition behind the Bayesian classifier.</p>\n<p>Bayesian classification is a form of probabilistic classification. Intuitively, when determining a line that separates the two classes, we look at the distribution of each class. What my friend intuitively focused on was the \"center\" or the mean and the \"spread\" or the standard deviation of the distribution. Another factor can be the prior of each class. For example, if there are more blue class to begin with, then we can think that blue class is more probable and the line would shift away from the blue class. Ok, now let's put these ideas into a more mathematically rigorous form.</p>\n<p>Giving a feature vector X, we want to find the most <strong>probable</strong> class. So if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>r</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P(blue|X) &gt; P(red|X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">b</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">u</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">e</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&gt;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">d</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, then X belongs to class blue, and red the other way around.</p>\n<h2>Discriminant function</h2>\n<h2>Linear vs quatric</h2>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.18229854689565%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"third\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/2e063bd8e3308e6488b3d0453fb5d50e/a66cd/third.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2e063bd8e3308e6488b3d0453fb5d50e/4272c/third.jpg 188w,\n/static/2e063bd8e3308e6488b3d0453fb5d50e/1459e/third.jpg 375w,\n/static/2e063bd8e3308e6488b3d0453fb5d50e/a66cd/third.jpg 750w,\n/static/2e063bd8e3308e6488b3d0453fb5d50e/c0626/third.jpg 1125w,\n/static/2e063bd8e3308e6488b3d0453fb5d50e/45751/third.jpg 1500w,\n/static/2e063bd8e3308e6488b3d0453fb5d50e/628ee/third.jpg 1514w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 64.46837146702558%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"fourth\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/dbc7640fd73bf4f9e3f8adecc82fabc4/a66cd/fourth.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/dbc7640fd73bf4f9e3f8adecc82fabc4/4272c/fourth.jpg 188w,\n/static/dbc7640fd73bf4f9e3f8adecc82fabc4/1459e/fourth.jpg 375w,\n/static/dbc7640fd73bf4f9e3f8adecc82fabc4/a66cd/fourth.jpg 750w,\n/static/dbc7640fd73bf4f9e3f8adecc82fabc4/c0626/fourth.jpg 1125w,\n/static/dbc7640fd73bf4f9e3f8adecc82fabc4/acbc3/fourth.jpg 1486w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<h2>Special case</h2>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"best-classifier"}}